cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GR 

This paper is about training neural networks using evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the trade-offs and performance of different optimization algorithms, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image classification tasks, specifically on the MNIST dataset, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm on the GPU, which is related to graphics (cs.GR).
